title: Shakespeare: The Complete Sonnets and Poems
description:
William Shakespeare: The Complete Sonnets and Poems
(Oxford World's Classics)
Edited by Colin Burrow

PDF, 761 pp.

Almost 200 pages of commentary provide a literary and biographical setting for the poems themselves.  Join me in hating the title, which should be "The Complete Sonnets and OTHER Poems," since sonnets themselves are poems.

This will be the last Shakespeare book I will share (at least until I find some more), so please check my torrents for a variety of reference books on Shakespeare and other topics.  Also, it bears repeating, at www.archive.org, you can find some incredible Shakespeare materials, including scans of very old books from very old British libraries.  As always, please seed.
